{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.11",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 11",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 11 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:1",
      "text": "Then Zophar, the Naamathite, answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:2",
      "text": "“Shouldn’t the multitude of words be answered? Should a man full of talk be justified?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:3",
      "text": "Should your boastings make men hold their peace? When you mock, will no man make you ashamed?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:4",
      "text": "For you say, ‘My doctrine is pure. I am clean in your eyes.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:5",
      "text": "But oh that God would speak, and open his lips against you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:6",
      "text": "that he would show you the secrets of wisdom! For true wisdom has two sides. Know therefore that God exacts of you less than your iniquity deserves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:7",
      "text": "“Can you fathom the mystery of God? Or can you probe the limits of the Almighty?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:8",
      "text": "They are high as heaven. What can you do? They are deeper than Sheol. What can you know?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:9",
      "text": "Its measure is longer than the earth, and broader than the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:10",
      "text": "If he passes by, or confines, or convenes a court, then who can oppose him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:11",
      "text": "For he knows false men. He sees iniquity also, even though he doesn’t consider it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:12",
      "text": "An empty-headed man becomes wise when a man is born as a wild donkey’s colt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:13",
      "text": "“If you set your heart aright, stretch out your hands toward him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:14",
      "text": "If iniquity is in your hand, put it far away. Don’t let unrighteousness dwell in your tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:15",
      "text": "Surely then you will lift up your face without spot. Yes, you will be steadfast, and will not fear,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:16",
      "text": "for you will forget your misery. You will remember it like waters that have passed away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:17",
      "text": "Life will be clearer than the noonday. Though there is darkness, it will be as the morning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:18",
      "text": "You will be secure, because there is hope. Yes, you will search, and will take your rest in safety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:19",
      "text": "Also you will lie down, and no one will make you afraid. Yes, many will court your favor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.11.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:20",
      "text": "But the eyes of the wicked will fail. They will have no way to flee. Their hope will be the giving up of the spirit.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
